1 under powers set out by any of subsections subdivisions (2) through (4) and (6) of this section, it
2 may as part of its decision charge the reasonable costs of investigation and hearing to the person
3 disciplined."
4 SECTION 4. G.S. 90-270.93 reads as rewritten:
5 "§ 90-270.93. Records to be kept; copies of record.
6 The Board shall keep a record of proceedings under this Article and a record of all persons
7 licensed under it. The record shall show the name, email, last known place of business and last
8 known place of residence, and date and number of licensure certificate as a physical therapist or
9 physical therapist assistant, for every living licensee. Any interested person in the State is entitled
10 to obtain a copy of that record on application to the Board and payment of such reasonable charge
11 as may be fixed by it based on the costs involved."
12 SECTION 5. G.S. 90-270.95 reads as rewritten:
13 "§ 90-270.95. Qualifications of applicants for examination; licensure; application; fee.
14 Any person who desires to be licensed under this Article and who:who meets all of the
15 following:
16 (1) Is of good moral character;character.
17 (2) If an applicant for physical therapy therapist licensure, has been graduated
18 from a physical therapy therapist program accredited by an agency recognized
19 by either the U.S. Office of Education or the Council on Postsecondary
20 Accreditation; andfor Higher Education Accreditation.
21 (3) If an applicant for physical therapist assistant licensure, licensure has been
22 graduated from a physical therapist assistant educational program accredited
23 by an agency recognized by either the U.S. Office of Education or the Council
24 on Postsecondary Accreditation;for Higher Education Accreditation, then the
25 applicant may make application on a form furnished byshall apply to the
26 Board for examination for licensure as a physical therapist or physical
27 therapist assistant. At the time of making such that application, the applicant
28 shall pay to the secretary-treasurer of the Board the fee prescribed by the
29 Board, no portion of which shall be returned."
30 SECTION 6. G.S. 90-270.96(a) reads as rewritten:
31 "(a) All applicants for licensure shall consent to a criminal history record check. Refusal
32 to consent to a criminal history record check may shall constitute grounds for the Board to deny
33 licensure to an applicant. The Board shall be responsible for providing to the State Bureau of
34 Investigation the fingerprints of the applicant to be checked, a form signed by the applicant
35 consenting to the criminal history record check and the use of fingerprints and other identifying
36 information required by the State or National Repositories, and any additional information
37 required by the State Bureau of Investigation. The Board shall keep all information obtained
38 pursuant to this section confidential."
