7 SECTION 8. G.S. 90-270.98 reads as rewritten:
8 "§ 90-270.98. Certificates of licensure.
9 (a) The Board shall furnish a certificate of licensure to each applicant successfully
10 passing the examination for licensure as a physical therapist or physical therapist assistant,
11 respectively. Upon receipt of satisfactory evidence that an applicant has graduated, within six
12 months prior to application, from a physical therapy or physical therapy assistant program
13 accredited as required under G.S. 90-270.95, the Board may authorize the applicant to perform
14 as a physical therapist or physical therapist assistant in this State, but only under the immediate
15 supervision of a physical therapist licensed in this State, until a formal decision by the Board on
16 the application for license. If a new graduate applicant that has been authorized to perform under
17 supervision by a licensed physical therapist fails (without due cause as determined in the Board's
18 discretion) to take the next succeeding examination, or if the applicant fails to pass the
19 examination, and consequently does not become licensed, the authorization for the applicant to
20 perform under supervision shall expire. Applicants approved by the Board for performance as
21 physical therapists or physical therapist assistants while their applications are pending under
22 circumstances described in this subsection shall be referred to as Physical Therapist Graduate or
23 Physical Therapist Assistant Graduate.respectively, and who satisfies the requirements of
24 G.S. 90-270.95.
25 (b) The Board shall furnish a certificate of licensure to any person who is a physical
26 therapist or physical therapist assistant registered or licensed under the laws of another state or
27 territory, if the individual's qualifications were at the date of his or her registration or licensure
28 substantially equal to the requirements under this Article.Article and if the individual satisfies
29 the requirements of G.S. 90-270.95. When making such application, the applicant shall pay to
30 the secretary-treasurer of the Board the fee prescribed by the Board, no portion of which shall be
31 returned."
32 SECTION 9. G.S. 90-270.99 reads as rewritten:
33 "§ 90-270.99. Renewal of license; lapse; revival.
34 (a) Every licensed physical therapist or physical therapist assistant shall, during the
35 month of Januaryfrom November 1 through January 31 at close of business of every year, apply
36 to the Board for a renewal of licensure and pay to the secretary-treasurer the prescribed fee. If
37 January 31 is not a business day, the renewal deadline shall be the next succeeding business day.
38 Licenses that are not so renewed shall automatically lapse. The Board may decline to renew
39 licenses of physical therapists or physical therapist assistants for failure to comply with any
40 required continuing competency measures.
41 (b) The manner in which lapsed licenses shall be revived, reinstated, or extended shall be
42 established by the Board in its discretion."
